# .cleo/.gitignore — Deny-by-default for CLEO project data
# Ignore everything, then explicitly allow only tracked files.
#
# ADR-013 §9 (2026-04-07, T5158): config.json + project-info.json are
# runtime snapshots regenerated by `cleo init`, not tracked in git.
# Recovery for all four runtime files (tasks.db, brain.db, config.json,
# project-info.json) is provided by `cleo backup add` snapshots under
# .cleo/backups/. See .cleo/adrs/ADR-013 for the full recovery story.

# Step 1: Ignore everything
*

# Allow list
!.gitignore
!project-context.json
!setup-otel.sh
!DATA-SAFETY-IMPLEMENTATION-SUMMARY.md
!adrs/
!adrs/**
!rcasd/
!rcasd/**
!agent-outputs/
!agent-outputs/**
# PSYCHE planning meta-docs with original source-project branding — local only (D032/D033)
# These docs reference the upstream psyche-lineage source tree verbatim and stay
# off GitHub per owner directive. The canonical SINGLE point of Honcho→PSYCHE
# translation is PORT-AND-RENAME-SYNTHESIS.md.
agent-outputs/T1075-psyche-integration-plan/PORT-AND-RENAME-SYNTHESIS.md
agent-outputs/T1075-psyche-integration-plan/PLAN.md
agent-outputs/T1075-psyche-integration-plan/PSYCHE-SOURCE-NOTES.md
agent-outputs/T1075-psyche-integration-plan/GLOSSARY.md
# V2026.4.110-RELEASE-PLAN is a planning artifact that references upstream source paths
agent-outputs/V2026.4.110-RELEASE-PLAN.md
# T1237: project-tier CANT agent personas (canonical post-T889).
# `.cleo/cant/agents/` is the ONLY canonical location for project-tier .cant
# personas. The legacy `.cleo/agents/` directory was removed in T1237.
!cant/
!cant/**

# Explicit deny safety net
*.db
*.db-shm
*.db-wal
*.db-journal
config.json
project-info.json
log.json
bypass-log.json
qa-log.json
.deps-cache/
.context-alert-state.json
.context-state*.json
context-states/
.git-checkpoint-state
.migration-state.json
migrations.json
sync/
metrics/
.backups/
backups/
